Stephenson County Farm Bureau(R)
August 7 at 10:58 AM 路

Today we say goodbye to our 2020 Summer Program Assistant, Kaylen Miller. Kaylen will head back to Iowa State University to complete her senior year. Orangeville Bronco Boosters
July 17 at 2:02 PM 路

Boosters are still holding out hope for a fall sports season! If you are looking for a way to support your favorite Bronco sports team while following mask guidelines that will likely be in place, or if you are looking to show school spirit when we return to the classroom, Boosters has a couple options available for you in both youth and adult sizes!! Order forms will be available in the High School Office starting Monday July 20th, at the Jr High/High School Sports meeting Monday night, or you can follow the link below to the Booster website and print one off. Orders and money will be due by Monday, July 27th at noon so that we can get them in before school and sports start. GO BRONCOS!!

https://sites.google.com/view/broncoboosters

post_text: Graduation will take place tomorrow evening on the football field. The ceremony begins at 6:30, and the field spaces have already been reserved for grad's families. We do have limited space on the bleachers and also room along the field for others, but bringing lawn chairs is suggested. ALSO, we must collect name/address/phone for anyone attending, so if you would like to save time when entering the gate, write this information down ahead of time & hand it in when you get there. Please bring masks for when social distancing cannot be preserved. For those who cannot attend, we do plan to post video of the ceremony this weekend.

post_text:
After considering a number of things, such as enrollment, future class sizes, & participation data, the athletic dept. determined it would not be possible to provide a true 11-man football program (gr 9-12) in the future at Orangeville with our current standing. There were two options available for consideration going forward. The following informational presentation goes over what was considered & the recommendation by the athletic dept. https://youtu.be/y4FdbIBV1p0
On Monday June 8th the Orangeville Board of Education voted to move our football program to 8-man beginning in the 2021-2022 school year.
text:
After considering a number of things, such as enrollment, future class sizes, & participation data, the athletic dept. determined it would not be possible to provide a true 11-man football program (gr 9-12) in the future at Orangeville with our current standing. There were two options available for consideration going forward. The following informational presentation goes over what was considered & the recommendation by the athletic dept. https://youtu.be/y4FdbIBV1p0
On Monday June 8th the Orangeville Board of Education voted to move our football program to 8-man beginning in the 2021-2022 school year.

post_text: Sharing this on behalf of the PTO: Teacher Appreciation week is the week of May 4  8th. It would be great if students would take time in the next couple weeks to send their teachers hand-written notes or cards. This school closure is just as difficult for them as it is for the students & parents. If you could snap a picture of your kid(s) holding a thank you sign of some sort, OR record a short video thanking their teacher(s), it would make our video super touching for the teachers. The pictures and videos can be emailed to the PTO's email address: OrangevillePTO@gmail.com. Deadline for the media submission is Friday May 1st.

Custer State Park
March 24 at 12:40 PM 路

Come one, come all!

Join us on a Virtual Field Trip tomorrow (Wed. March 25) at 10:00 a.m. MT on Facebook Live to learn all about our bison herd!

See you tomorrow!

#HiFromSD #SDInTheField #DiscoverBlackHills

Orangevilles Tessa Janecke wrapped up her sophomore season with the NAHA Winterhawks in the Junior Womens Hockey League with being named to the 1st team all star roster and then today winning the U19 league championship 6-2 over the Ottawa Lady 67s. post_text: Hockey Announcement: The Fury won Sectionals on Friday night vs the Fond Du Lac Warbirds. They are the #4 seed for State Finals, and will play #1 seed Madison Metro Lynx at 4pm on Thursday, in the State Semifinals at the Alliant Center in Madison. If they win, they will play Saturday the 7th around noon at the Alliant Center. Any student who wishes to go and cheer on Anna Malone and her team on Thursday's Semifinals will be allowed to leave school at 2pm. You must have a note from a parent to receive a yellow slip. Mr. Janecke will be taking attendance once at the alliant Center.

February 9 at 5:45 PM 路

The Lena-Winslow/Orangeville Speech Team had an amazing season this year! Everyone did an amazing job at the Regional meet yesterday. The following earned a space in the top four to move on to Sectionals in Freeport next week:
Kierra/Rowen Schulz - 1st place Humorous Duet Acting
Kierra Schulz - 3rd place Humorous Interpretation
Jennifer Swedlund - 3rd place Informative Speaking
Lucas Schoaf - 4th place Original Comedy
Alysse Potter - 4th place Original Oratory
Ronan O'Brien - 2nd place Radio Speaking
The team took 5th place and the additional members placed:
Nick Swedlund - 6th place Extemporaneous Speaking
Braden Baldauf - 7th place Special Occasion Speaking
Kasey Morgan - 5th place Impromptu Speaking

post_text: ぉ On behalf of Nationwide Inbound, our 4th grade teacher Stacey Brown has been chosen as the Teacher of the Month out of the many represented schools within the Stephenson, Ogle, Carroll, and Winnebago Counties. Stacey was recognized for exemplifying outstanding performance within a teaching role, promoting and being a strong advocate for teamwork, and for inspiring excellence in others. Earlier today, Nationwide Inbound surprised her in front of her students with a certificate and gift. Congrats Stacey!

post_text: Great job Ronan!
shared_text:
Lena-Winslow/Orangeville High School Speech Team
December 8, 2019 at 8:51 PM 路

Congratulations to the Lena-
Winslow/Orangeville Speech team for placing 2nd at the Stockton Pow Wow Tournament this weekend. The following placed in their categories:
Dramatic Interpretation - Payton Scace - 5th place
Extemporaneous Speaking - Ben Gardner - 4th place, Nick Swedlund - 6th place
Humorous Duet Acting - Lucas Schoaf and Braden Baldauf - 5th place
Impromptu Speaking - Ronan O'Brien - 3rd place
Informative Speaking - Jennifer Swedlund - 3rd place
Oratorical Declamation - Mikhail Schoonhoven-Hussian - 5th place
Original Comedy - Lucas Schoaf - 4th place
Original Oratory - Alysse Potter - 3rd place
Poetry - Jacob Malloy - 5th place
Prose - Andrea Sutter - 1st place and Judges Preference Award
Radio Speaking - Ronan O'Brien - 1st place, Braden Baldauf - 5th place, and Nick Swedlund - 6th place
Special Occasion Speaking - Ben Gardner - 4th place.
This group of individuals has been working very hard and did an amazing job on Saturday. They will compete next week at the Rochelle Tournament.

The Board of Education of the Orangeville CUSD #203 is accepting immediate applications for the following position for the 2019-2020 school year:

Assistant Jr. High Girls Basketball Coach

Qualifications: Interested individuals must possess high level coaching skills and experience, specific sport knowledge, and high-level personal experience in playing the sport. All coaches should commit to developing young athletes to be competent, responsible young men/women and better players.
Send letter of application, coaching resume and coaching philosophy to:
Apply in writing via mail or email to:
Mr. William Guy, Athletic Director
Orangeville High School
201 S. Orange St. Orangeville, IL 61060
(815)789-4289 ext 205
Email address: wguy@orangevillecusd.com
